<figureCitation box="[255,297,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="105.[151,250,1833,1857]" captionTargetBox="[175,1420,203,1797]" captionTargetId="figure-19@105.[151,1436,181,1809]" captionTargetPageId="105" captionText="FIGURE 11. Mesoventrite of males of: a) Belonuchus cariniventris, b) B. oxyporinus, c) B. rufisternus, d) B. tepoztecus, e) B. bidens, f) B. jalappensis, g) B. longitarsus, h) B. ephippiatus, i) B. dichrous, j) B. flavipennis, k) B. platypterus, l) B. juanmorronei, m) B. iridescens. Red arrow: intercoxal process of the mesoventrite, blue arrow: transverse discal ridge, green arrow: longitudinal carina in anterior half." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6630913" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6630913/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">11a</figureCitation>
, 17f, 18c, 21c, 26b
</paragraph>
